@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<div class="header">
    <h3>Data Dash Privacy Policy</h3>
    <p>Your data security is important to us. Please take the time to review this privacy policy.</p>
</div>

<div class="content">
    <h5>1. Data Collection</h5>
    <p>We collect personal data to provide and improve our services. Personal data includes your name, email address, phone number, and other data that you choose to provide to us. This data may be collected through the use of our services, or from third-party providers. </p>

    <h5>2. Data Use</h5>
    <p>We use personal data for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide and improve our services.</li>
        <li>To respond to customer inquiries and provide support.</li>
        <li>To monitor and analyze usage for improving our services.</li>
        <li>To protect the security and integrity of our services.</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>3. Data Security</h5>
    <p>We use industry-standard security measures to protect personal data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. We limit access to personal data to employees who need to know that information in order to provide products or services to you. </p>

    <h5>4. Data Sharing</h5>
    <p>We do not sell or share personal data with third parties. However, we may share aggregated or de-identified data with third parties for research purposes. </p>

    <h5>5. Data Retention</h5>
    <p>We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy. </p>

    <h5>6. Your Rights</h5>
    <p>You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal data at any time. Please contact us to exercise these rights. </p>

    <h5>7. Children's Privacy</h5>
    <p>We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under the age of 13. If you believe we have collected personal data from a child under 13, please contact us immediately. </p>

    
</div>



